					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on the book of Proverbs.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="95v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Proverbs</title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>An anonymous Arabic commentary on Proverbs, chapters 1:22-8:34, 24:28-25:11.</p>
								<p>The Hebrew text is quoted in part and written in square characters.</p>
								<p>There is an Arabix translation arranged in the following sections: chapter 2; 3:1-18; 3:19-35; 4:1-19; 4:20-27; 5; 6:1-5; 6:6-11; 6:12-19; 6:20-35; 7; 8:1-21; 8:22-36; 25:1-13. The beginning of each section is marked by the word נץ in the margin.</p>
								<p>Scant masoretic notes.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Partially agrees with Or 2508, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">338</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of approximately 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>95 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>122</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>95 folios (+2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>10 quires, nos. 2-10, and folios 88-95, the numeration of which is uncertain.</p>
									<p>Nos. 2, 10 and the last one are imperfect.</p>
									<p>Signatures in Arabic words on the upper margin of the first folio, and the four following folios are numbered with Arabic numerals. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Leaves missing after folios 8 and 87.</p>
									<p>Folios 1, 2, 15, 53, 54, 62, 65, 71, 76, 79, 80, 88, 90, 91 are damaged.</p>
									<p>Greater part of folio 87 is lost.</p>
									<p>Many folios worm-eaten.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="15" writtenLines="15">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
